cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a problem in wireless networks and proposes a solution to improve their performance. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category as the paper involves optimizing the transmission of packets in a wireless network. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper may involve the transmission of multimedia data over wireless networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper may involve security issues related to wireless networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper may involve control mechanisms to improve the performance of wireless networks.
